## Summary of SKILL.md

This is the master standard document for building **mini-theory-of-computation** — a collection of self-contained mini-modules covering computation/complexity theory. Key sections:

### §0 — Dual Standard Principle
Every sub-module must meet **two independent conditions**:
- **Entry condition**: Each `mini-xxx/` sub-module must have ≥ **3,000 lines** of code (`include/` + `src/`), excluding `.lean`, tests, and examples.
- **Completion condition**: Nine knowledge levels L1-L6 **Complete** + L7-L9 **Partial+**.

### §1-2 — Nine-Level Knowledge System (L1→L9)
| Level | Name |
|-------|------|
| L1 | Definitions |
| L2 | Core Concepts |
| L3 | Mathematical Structures |
| L4 | Fundamental Laws (theorems) |
| L5 | Algorithms/Methods |
| L6 | Canonical Problems |
| L7 | Applications |
| L8 | Advanced Topics |
| L9 | Research Frontiers |

### §3 — Nine-School Curriculum Benchmarking
Aligns with courses from **MIT, Stanford, Berkeley, CMU, Princeton, Caltech, Cambridge, Oxford, ETH**.

### §4 — Forbidden Behaviors
- Code quality violations (stubs, no implementations, skipped edge cases, etc.)
- **Anti-Filler Iron Law** — prohibits bulk-generating function stubs to pad line counts
- Lean 4 formalization rules (no `sorry`, no `by trivial`, no cross-file copy-paste)

### §5-6 — Mandatory Artifacts & Completion Criteria
Each sub-module must produce: `Makefile`, `README.md`, `include/`, `src/`, `tests/`, `examples/`, `demos/`, `benches/`, `docs/` with 5 knowledge documents.

### §7 — Directory Structure
```
0. mini-complexity-foundations/   (cook-levin, P-NP, time-hierarchy, space-hierarchy, etc.)
1. mini-circuit-complexity/       (boolean-circuits, ac0-nc, switching-lemma, etc.)
2. mini-algorithmic-complexity/   (future: PCP, IP=PSPACE, fine-grained, etc.)
```

### §8-9 — Audit Process & Self-Check
A Python-based `deep_audit.py` script template for automated scoring. Maximum score = 18 (2 pts per level × 9). COMPLETE requires ≥16/18.

### §10 — Safety Review
Grep-based scans for filler patterns, stubs, empty files, and knowledge document completeness. **Zero tolerance** for filler code.

### §11 — Reference Textbooks
Arora & Barak, Sipser, Goldreich, Papadimitriou, Moore & Mertens, Vollmer, Jukna, O'Donnell, Vazirani, Nielsen & Chuang, and others.

---

The file serves as the **gold standard** — any sub-module must pass all audits before being declared `COMPLETE`.
